snippet.title: INDOOR PLAYGROUND Family Fun Play Area with Kids Toys and Ball Pit in Kids Channel Amusement Park
snippet.description:
INDOOR PLAYGROUND Family Fun Play Area with Kids Toys and Ball Pit in Kids Channel Amusement Park.
https://youtu.be/5VkJS76ydIE

This is one of the biggest name of indoor playground for kids in Malaysia, JKids Playground. Miqael really love it here and playing here almost 4 hours non stop most every week. This place is really fun. Enjoy the clips my friends. This is FUN!!

What is Indoor Playground
Indoor playgrounds, also known as indoor play centers, are playgrounds located in interior environment. They are specifically designed for kids to play in and have tremendous fun with. The soft-contained structure and play equipment are wrapped in soft foam to absorb the impact when children fall or bounce around. As such, an indoor playground is usually a safer play area compared to an outdoor playground.

Since its origination in 1990′s from the US, indoor playground has enjoyed immense popularity all over the world. Today, it has evolved from simple indoor climbing frame, to complex children play center that includes multiple play areas serving different age groups. In addition to ticket sales, the revenue of indoor playground comes from a diverse source of children’s entertainment and services such as: hosting party, gift sale, kids art and craft, drinks, and more.

Indoor playgrounds can vary hugely in terms of sizes and play features. while small indoor playground may be mainly a soft-contained play structure, Large indoor playgrounds, sometimes a part of a family entertainment center, can span across over 1000 square metres, and include the following sections:

Indoor play structure:
Traditional indoor play structure, often referred as soft play area or indoor climbing frame, is indispensable to any indoor playground. They can be as simple as a small soft play structure with basic play events like a slide and a ball pool, or a complicated multi-level play system that includes hundreds of play events and features custom-built theme elements.

The difference between “indoor play structure” and “custom indoor playground” is that the later includes more play area or function area such as cafe area, thus is a complete indoor play center.

4 levels indoor play structure  Wave slide of indoor play structure  Soft-contained indoor play structure  Installing multiple level indoor play structure

Interactive soft play:
As opposed to the static traditional soft play, interactive soft play equipment are installed with electronic components such as motor, LED lights, speakers and sensors, thus offer greater interactivity and a more engaging play experience, it is also called electric soft play. Interactive soft play is favorite play events of children between 2-6.
Electric soft play area in the indoor playground   Balloon carnival interactive softplay equipment  electric softplay spinning octopus 4  Interactive soft play - Spinning Cups

Ball blaster area:
Ball blaster, also known as ballocity or ball battle, is a self-contained play area that is installed with many guns, cannon, and other play equipment that shoot foam balls. Ball blaster attracts more 6-12 years old children than any other play equipment. Indoor playground with a ball blaster area commands a higher attendance, and receives more repeat visits.
ball blaster area in Amusement park  Ball blaster guns on the second floor  automatic ball blaster gun  ball cannon for indoor playground

Toddler area:
The toddler’s area features toddler children’s favorite play equipment such as mini slide, soft play toys, play panels, large building blocks, ball pool, kids pretend play, and other toys used in pretending games. Some electric soft play equipments are also perfect for the toddler area.
Indoor playground toddler area  Toddler indoor play area  Softplay for kids play area - star  Kids playhouse - post office

snippet.title: Toy Story 3

In Toy Story 3, Woody (voiced by Tom Hanks), Buzz Lightyear (voiced by Tim Allen) and the rest of the Toy Story gang return for an all-new adventure, along with a few new faces – some plastic, some plush – including Barbie's counterpart Ken (voiced by Michael Keaton), a thespian hedgehog named Mr. Pricklepants (voiced by Timothy Dalton) and a strawberry-scented bear named Lots-o'-Huggin' Bear (voiced by Ned Beatty). It's "the biggest, best, most exciting Toy Story of them all," raves Access Hollywood's Scott Mantz.As Andy prepares to depart for college, Woody, Buzz, Jessie and the rest of Andy's faithful toys wonder what will become of them. But, when a mix-up lands them at Sunnyside Daycare, they meet a host of new toys and soon discover a wild new adventure is just beginning!

snippet.title: Declutering Kids Toys - 6 steps in 15 minutes
snippet.description:
#Declutering #toys #Kenyanvlog #simpleliving 

If there is an area in my house I have found difficult to declutter is my child’s toys. I have kept postponing this exercise for the longest time. I however asked my daughter one time if she could give out her toys to other children who didn’t have and she said no. she told me “they are mine, they are not for them”. She was young though,  she had just turned 3 years. I realised that she didn’t understand what giving to the needy meant and it has been a journey since then. 

So today we are almost 4 years and we got to do some toy decluttering.

This is how it started:

I was leaving my bedroom ending to the kitchen then I thought “Shani needs to colour, I haven’t seen her colour in a while”. So I decided to get the colours for her to do the colouring…. Wacha nitafute (then I looked for) the colours! There is this big bag where she puts her toys and the bag was just so full. After a long search I decided to do the necessary. I called up Shani and agreed that we were going to sort out her toys. 

Here’s what we did:

1. We had a chat on how we were going to do the decluttering. We decided that we were going to choose the toys she uses most often and keep them. The toys she doesn’t use and feels like she can give away, we were going to keep them on a corner somewhere for “giving”, then later put them in a bag and give them out. The ones that are spoiled we were going to throw them away.  This discussion was made easy by our family lifestyle of simple living. Shani has seen me Vlog on decluttering, tidying up, giving and saving money. Some Vlogs I have done with her and so she could associate with simple living values. 

2. We then picked the toy bag, lifted it up and poured everything on the floor.

3. We picked one garbage bag for putting up the toys for giving away. The broken ones we just picked one of the toy bags we were going to dispose and made it home for the spoiled ones. 

4. We then started sorting out the toys. We picked each toy, in fact the word is touched. I lifted each toy and asked Shani which bag it was going to. She then picked the item from me and evaluated it then put it on the right bag. All this time we talking about it. Who are we going to give it to? And Shani agreed that our house help who has a granddaughter needed some of the toys then the rest we could give to another children’s home.

5. So then we packed Shani's toys in smaller boxes (those that needed to be in a box) and then put them in her big toy bag.

6. We asked Josephine (house help) to come pick toys for her grandchild and then we packed the rest and put in a bag that we are taking to the children's home. We also disposed the spoiled toys.

Rodney and his pals take on the evil corporate tyrant Ratchet (Greg Kinnear) to prove that "you can shine no matter what you're made of".

snippet.title: Toys Are Not For Children
snippet.description: Psychological trauma and aberrant sexuality abound in this twisted 1972 tale of a young woman whose severe daddy issues send her on an unforgettably bleak downward spiral. Yearning for the love of her absentee father, Jamie inhabits an infantilised world surrounded by toys, including those which her wayward pops bizarrely continues to send her. Unable to consummate her new marriage with dashing colleague Charlie, Jamie's chance encounter with aging sex worker Pearl leads her into the murky world of prostitution where her most disturbing erotic fantasies begin to play out. Grim, quirky and strangely affecting in equal measure, Stanley H. Brasloff's 'Toys Are Not for Children' is a truly one-of-a-kind effort from the heyday of the American exploitation independents, which builds to a haunting and devastating climax that lingers long after the credits roll.
